description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

--
Kenendy does monologue on the newly released information on Osama Bin Laden. He was a fan of Noam Chomsky and apparently a 9/11 truther. (WTF?)

Tonights panel MICHAEL C. MOYNIHAN, MIKE BAKER, and TOM SHILLUE stop in to discuss the new Bin Laden documents, ACLU and the Tea Party make ad to advocate against the NSA. (With MIKE BAKER on the panel, imagine that.)

The panel returns to talk about Bill Clinton predicting Martin O'Malley "would go all the way" in regards to becoming president. Scott Walker thinks that dropping out of college will help him in the 2016 elections.

RONDA ROUSEY is interviewed by Kennedy.

Topical Storm
Bill Murray drinks vodka on Letterman, falls down.
First Lady gets physical. 
KFC practices necromancy and brings Col. Sanders back from the dead.

The panel returns to discuss capping ex-presidential spending caps. Vendor selling 30 dollar hot dogs at Ground Zero. Women has baby at 65.


STEPHEN HAYES and JONATHAN LAST stop by to dicuss their book The Dadly Virtues.

Tonight on Nightcap Kennedy talks about corruption within some prominent cancer charities.
